      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 42: The new TLS option `tlsDisableSecureDlgCheck` defaults to `true`, which means the UI can present and potentially persist an insecure SIP/TLS setting before account config is loaded or when the key is absent. A security-bypass option should default to the safe value and only be enabled explicitly from persisted configuration. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n    @Published var tlsDisableSecureDlgCheck: Bool \u003d false\n```",
